com.davidsoergel.trees
Class BasicPhylogenyNode<T extends Serializable>

java.lang.Object
  com.davidsoergel.trees.BasicPhylogenyNode<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
HierarchyNode<T,PhylogenyNode<T>>, LengthWeightHierarchyNode<T,PhylogenyNode<T>>, PhylogenyNode<T>, SerializablePhylogenyNode<T>, Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<PhylogenyNode<T>>
public class BasicPhylogenyNode<T extends Serializable>
extends Object
implements SerializablePhylogenyNode<T>

A basic implementation of the PhylogenyNode interface, where the generic type indicates the type of node IDs that are used (typically Strings or Integers).

getRandomLeafBelow

public PhylogenyNode<T> getRandomLeafBelow()
Note this samples from the distribution of leaves weighted by the tree structure, i.e. uniformly _per level_, not uniformly from the set of leaves. Basically, leaves with fewer siblings and cousins are more likely to be chosen.

depthFirstIterator

public DepthFirstTreeIterator<T,PhylogenyNode<T>> depthFirstIterator()
Get an iterator that returns all the nodes of the tree in depth-first order. The breadth ordering may or may not be defined, depending on the HierarchyNode implementation. We provide this depth-first iterator explicitly even though the HierarchyNode is itself iterable, because the default iterator may be breadth-first or something else.

Specified by:
depthFirstIterator in interface HierarchyNode<T extends Serializable,PhylogenyNode<T extends Serializable>>

the DepthFirstTreeIterator
